SIMPLE: runaway
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Runaway
<hw>Run"a*way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, flees from danger, duty, restraint, etc.; a
fugitive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou <qex>runaway</qex>, thou coward, art thou fled?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of running away, esp. of a horse or teams;
<as>as, there was a <ex>runaway</ex> yesterday</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Runaway</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Runaway
<hw>Run"a*way`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Running away;
fleeing from danger, duty, restraint, etc.; <as>as, <ex>runaway</ex>
soldiers; a <ex>runaway</ex> horse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accomplished by running away or elopement, or during
flight; <as>as, a <ex>runaway</ex> marriage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- <sn>3.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Won by a long lead; <as>as, a
<ex>runaway</ex> victory</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Very successful;
accomplishing success quickly; <as>as, a <ex>runaway</ex>
bestseller</as>.</def> --> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Runcation</ent>⟦br⟧
